## 3. Tier-conditional expectations

### 3.1 MIN-VIABLE

Three seats: {{LEAD_SEAT_NAME}}, {{BUILDER_SEAT_NAME}}, and a Contract-floor reviewer. This is the
whole roster — read the list below as what is genuinely **absent**, not abbreviated.

- **No watchdog seat.** There is no Monitor and no stall-watchdog autopilot. Liveness is
  **{{LEAD_SEAT_NAME}}-reconciler-only**: the Lead re-checks run status on every one of its own
  wakes, and that is the entire backstop. A stall that never wakes the Lead at all has no second
  line of defense at this tier.
- **No QA seat.** There is no dedicated end-to-end verification pass. The Contract-floor review
  is the only bench check a change gets before delivery.
- **No harvest loop.** There is no Mentor, no Coach, and no retro/harvest ledger. Nothing gets
  proposed as a new skill, nothing gets written to durable memory as a lesson, and nobody teaches
  the human engineer anything back. Every EARNED slot in §4 below stays empty indefinitely at
  this tier — there is no mechanism installed that could ever fill them.
- **Single-family bench — the cross-family guarantee is explicitly FORFEITED.** This squad's
  core reviewer-diversity thesis is that a bench spanning ≥2 model families distinct from the
  Builder/Lead family catches blind spots a single family shares with the seat that wrote the
  code. MIN-VIABLE runs exactly one reviewer. That thesis **cannot hold** with a bench of one,
  and this tier does not claim it does. If a shared-family blind spot getting through review
  unchallenged is a risk you're not willing to carry, this is the signal to upgrade to STANDARD
  or FULL (§6), not a gap to work around with prompting.

### 3.2 STANDARD *(adds, on top of everything in 3.1)*

Adds four seats — {{QA_SEAT_NAME}}, a binding-veto Security reviewer, an Architecture
coherence-flag reviewer, and {{MONITOR_SEAT_NAME}} — plus the full risk-routing glob set (MIN-VIABLE
only routes the Contract floor + docs-allowlist) and the drift-audit's MCP lane + the watchdog
autopilot.

- **Security and Contract now both hold binding vetoes; Architecture is a weighted coherence
  flag, not a veto.** (This assignment is a fixed default, not a per-squad choice — see
  `constitution.md`'s mention directory for the canonical statement.)
- **{{MONITOR_SEAT_NAME}} is issue-gated, not always-on.** The Lead arms its autopilot at
  readiness PASS and re-arms it every wake; the Monitor self-pauses the moment the board goes
  idle. It is a backstop for the stall class that never wakes the Lead at all — it does not
  replace the Lead's own reconciler from 3.1, it sits behind it.
- **The reviewer bench now spans ≥2 model families distinct from the Builder/Lead family** — the
  cross-family guarantee that MIN-VIABLE explicitly forfeits (3.1) is live at this tier. Install
  refuses at P0 if the probed catalog can't actually seat ≥2 distinct reviewer-capable families;
  it does not silently degrade to a weaker bench.
- **MCP-usage prune sweep — actually run it.** Every seat's MCP server set ships broad-then-prune
  on purpose (installer principle: no bespoke config authored at install beyond the one
  sanctioned MCP-authoring surface). "Broad" is the easy half; "prune" only happens if you run
  `audit-drift.sh`'s MCP lane on a cadence and act on its drop-if-still-zero-at-next-audit
  tripwire. Skip this and the install stays broad forever — the servers a seat never calls sit
  there as unused surface area, which is exactly the outcome the prune sweep exists to prevent.

### 3.3 FULL *(adds, on top of everything in 3.1 + 3.2)*

Adds a Validator (Phase 1.5, advisory-only, never a veto), {{MENTOR_SEAT_NAME}}, and — only if you
opted in at interview Q2 — {{COACH_SEAT_NAME}}.

- **{{VALIDATOR_SEAT_NAME}} is advisory only and ships behind its own sunset tripwire.** It fires
  narrowly (a groundable runtime/boot or external-SDK claim the readiness check can't verify
  statically), never vetoes the readiness call, and is pre-committed to a KEEP/SUNSET decision
  read off the validation ledger on {{CONTROL_ISSUE_KEY}}, independent of whether it "feels"
  useful. Its own card (`validator.md`) is the source of truth for the exact tripwire criteria —
  this runbook does not restate them so the two can't drift apart.
- **Only FULL ships the learning loop — and only FULL gets to claim it "earns everything else."**
  {{MENTOR_SEAT_NAME}}'s skill-harvest, the review-quality-metrics scorecard, and the
  squad-measurement telemetry are what actually fill the EARNED slots described in §4. At
  MIN-VIABLE and STANDARD those slots are not merely unfilled today — there is no mechanism
  installed that will ever fill them, because the loop that does the filling doesn't exist below
  FULL. Every claim this squad makes about "specialization compounds over time" is a FULL-tier
  claim; do not expect it below FULL.
- **{{COACH_SEAT_NAME}} teaches the human, not the agents** — an inverted audience from
  {{MENTOR_SEAT_NAME}}. It mines the same delivered-parent window for human-learnable lessons and
  posts one learning issue per harvest window. Its worked teaching examples ship empty (§4) and
  fill in only after it actually runs a coaching pass.
- **The harvest ledger lives on {{CONTROL_ISSUE_KEY}}.** Delivered parents accumulate there and
  flush as one batched {{MENTOR_SEAT_NAME}} + {{COACH_SEAT_NAME}} delegation once the ledger holds
  enough of them (or you ask for an early flush) — never one harvest issue per delivery.

