## 4. Day-0 is untuned

This install shipped **zero** bespoke, project-tuned content. Everything below is an intentional
gap the retro/harvest loop fills from your squad's own real deliveries — not an oversight, and
not something to hand-write yourself. Filling any of these in by hand defeats the point: the
value of an EARNED slot is that it's grounded in a real incident on your project, not a plausible
guess made at install time.

- **Reviewer bug-class catalogs and named incident/race inventories** (the security reviewer's
  ranked bug-family list, the architecture reviewer's layer-chain + named races) ship as a
  generic seed only. They fill in as {{MENTOR_SEAT_NAME}} retrospects real findings *(FULL only —
  see 3.3; below FULL these stay generic forever)*.
- **Incident anecdotes inside operational skills** (e.g. the panel-degradation-recovery skill's
  worked example) ship with the method but no anecdote. One fills in the first time your squad
  actually lives through the failure the method exists for.
- **Any `{{SEAT_PREFIX}}-`-namespaced harvested skill.** The skill registry ships with zero
  project-namespaced skills on day 0 by design — every one you'll eventually see under that
  prefix is a skill-harvest proposal {{MENTOR_SEAT_NAME}} raised and a member authorized, never a
  pre-seeded guess *(FULL only)*.
- **A project-specific wire-oracle skill for {{QA_SEAT_NAME}}.** The oracle *method* (how to build
  a composition/outbound oracle) ships inside `qa.md` from day 0; the actual inventory of this
  project's wire surfaces to apply it to does not, and is earned once QA needs one for real.
- **`apply-roster.sh`'s migration history.** It ships as a clean provisioner with no rebuild/A-B
  log — every future roster surgery appends its own entry starting from this install, never
  backfilled from any prior squad's history.
- **Coach's worked judgment examples and calibration teach-set** *(FULL, opt-in only)* — ship
  empty; they fill the first time {{COACH_SEAT_NAME}} runs a real coaching pass on a real
  delivery.
- **This runbook's own §8 incident ledger and §9 see-also, below** — filled by you and by the
  retro loop as real decisions and cross-references accumulate. There is nothing to read there
  yet.
- **The MCP "prune" half of broad-then-prune** *(STANDARD+ only — §3.2)* — every seat starts on
  the full P0-probed catalog; which servers actually get used, and therefore which get dropped,
  is measured, not guessed, starting from your squad's first real runs.

