## 6. Re-scan cadence (P7 upgrade mode)

Everything this install derived by scanning your repo (commands, globs, branch names, CI check
names, and the rest of the 18 scan holes) is a snapshot taken at P1. Repos drift; scanned facts
go stale. P7 re-scan/upgrade mode re-runs the P1 scan on demand or on a cadence, diffs the fresh
values against the recorded hole store, and — only after you confirm what actually drifted —
re-emits the affected templates. That re-emission goes through the earned-content merge: every
live fenced EARNED region (§4) is extracted before re-emission and re-injected after, and a
re-emit that would shrink or drop a non-empty EARNED region is a hard failure, not a silent
overwrite. P7 is also how you move up a tier (MIN-VIABLE → STANDARD → FULL) later without losing
anything §4 has already earned you.

